Setup a virtual environments using conda

Requirement: anaconda python distribution installed and accessible

1.Update conda:
   conda update conda
2.Create avirtual environment for your project 
  conda create -n yourenvname python=x.x anaconda 
3.Use virtual environment 
  source activate yourenvname
4.Install required packages 
  conda install -n yourenvname packagename  
5.Deactivate virtual environment
  source deactivate 
6.Delete the virtual environment
  conda remove -n yourenvname -all
